## Compiling ##
###############
Our project can be compiled by simply entering 'make' in the
root directory of our project on any CCIS Linux machine. This
will automatically create an executable called 'spims' which
can be invoked exactly as shown on the Assignment 5 page:
http://www.ccs.neu.edu/course/cs4500wc/assignment5.txt

For each invocation of spims, a pattern and a source must be
specified. The pattern and source can either be single images
or directories containing only image files at the top level.

For example:

./spims -p /course/cs4500wc/Assignments/A4/Patterns/black.jpg \
        -s /course/cs4500wc/Assignments/A4/Sources/bb0001.jpg

...specifies that the program be run on a single pattern image
and a single source image...


./spims -pdir /course/cs4500wc/Assignments/A5/Patterns \
        -s /course/cs4500wc/Assignments/A5/Sources/greenish.png

...specifies that the program be run on a directory of pattern
images and a single source image...


./spims -p /course/cs4500wc/Assignments/A5/Patterns/green23.png \
        -sdir /course/cs4500wc/Assignments/A4/Sources

...specifies that the program be run on a single pattern image
and a directory of source images...


./spims -pdir /course/cs4500wc/Assignments/A5/Patterns \
        -sdir /course/cs4500wc/Assignments/A4/Sources

...specifies that the program be run on a directory of pattern
images and a directory or source images.


